reviewText: We loved this video. The children and I felt like we were at a stage show. It's just cute. There's also an educational element that will leave you more knowledgeable of some cat breeds. It was so enjoyable to watch the cats. The music and narration was cute too. This is a video to remind you that life is short, so enjoy it and love it. You'll learn something too.
summary: Fun, cute and clever as a cat

reviewText: Kitty Party is pretty much that...a DVD filled of footage of adorable kittens..romping, playing, tumblingaround and all in all being kittens. Very adorable.The IE Twins enjoyed Kitten Party because they love animals. But, it was not a video where they sat downand attentively watched it straight though. Rather they were busy playing and coloring while the videowas on and on occasion would look up and say "aw[...]".The twins are 7 so it may be a video geared for younger children that would more attentively watchthe DVD from start to finish. We did review Puppy Party about a year ago and that particular video waswatched from start to finish and over again...so it is only my speculation that the girls are now too old. Itmight be that they love doggies more then kittens.I would definitely pick this up for a toddler or preschooler. It would work great as an intro video for ababysitter or Sunday school as well.Overall I thought it was a sweet DVD.
summary: Very Adorable. Perfect for Younger Children

reviewText: Got my Brother-in-Law this as one of his birthday presents this year and its a winner.  If you know someone who loves cats or someone like me who just loves kittens you cannot go wrong with this.  Come on, little bundles of fur capering about madly!  Gonna grab a copy for myself now of this and that puppy one, figure its a spirit lifter for those crappy days.
